      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=2).",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from NAFEMS and ASME V&V 10 test suite were used to verify the structural solver for large-deformation contact mechanics relevant to the pedicle screw model. All benchmark results within 1% of analytical or reference solutions. Three independent analysts reproduced results."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=2). Mesh convergence study demonstrating <5% change in QoIs upon refinement.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the screw-rod-vertebral body assembly. QoIs (stiffness, yield force) changed by <3.2% between the medium and fine mesh, confirming convergence. Final mesh density: ~180,000 elements (C3D8R hex-dominant with C3D10 tetrahedral transitions at complex geometry)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=2). Residual norms and energy balance documented.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver convergence verified via force and displacement residual norms (<1e-4 relative tolerance). Energy balance error <0.1% across all load steps. Augmented Lagrange contact stabilization with penalty stiffness sensitivity study confirmed solution insensitivity to contact parameters within ±20% variation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=2). Independent review of model setup and boundary conditions.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by a second analyst not involved in original construction. Boundary conditions, load application, and material assignment verified against the ASTM F1717 test protocol and device drawings. No discrepancies identified. Review documented in internal technical memorandum TM-2023-047."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=3). Justification for constitutive model selection and contact formulation.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity (Ti-6Al-4V: E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, tangent modulus=1.2 GPa) selected based on published material characterization data and validated against coupon-level tensile tests. Frictional contact (mu=0.2, titanium-on-titanium) consistent with literature. Model form appropriate for quasi-static large-deformation structural response."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=3). Uncertainty in material properties and geometry quantified and propagated.",
      "rationale": "Material property uncertainty (±5% on E, ±3% on sigma_y) and geometric tolerance uncertainty (±0.05 mm on screw diameter) propagated via Monte Carlo simulation (N=500 runs). Combined input uncertainty contributes uval = 4.1% to QoI predictions, incorporated into the E/uval acceptance criterion evaluation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=3). Samples representative of production lot; dimensional inspection documented.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes). All specimens from the same production lot; dimensional inspection confirmed compliance with drawing tolerances. Coefficient of variation in experimental stiffness = 4.8%, indicating acceptable sample-to-sample consistency."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=3). Multiple test conditions spanning the clinical use envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard test configuration (static compression-bending, 10 mm offset). Only one loading condition evaluated; the clinical use envelope includes dynamic fatigue and varied offset distances not covered. This factor falls below the required level 3, representing a known gap acknowledged in the credibility assessment. Accepted under the overall framework given medium model influence and corroborating experimental agreement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=3). FEA inputs demonstrably matched to experimental specimen parameters.",
      "rationale": "FEA model geometry directly derived from CAD drawings of the tested production-lot specimens. Material properties assigned from lot-specific coupon test data provided by DePuy Synthes. Torque preload on set screws replicated in model via bolt pretension elements calibrated to measured installation torque (4.0 Nm). Input parameter equivalency confirmed by cross-laboratory comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=3). Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) applied to all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. Normalized validation metric E/uval computed per ASME V&V 40 Appendix B. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 (values: 1.41, 1.63, 1.78 respectively). Percentage differences all below the 10% pre-established acceptance bound. Graphical load-displacement curve overlay confirms qualitative agreement throughout the loading history."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=3). QoIs directly linked to clinical performance and regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary mechanical performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal fixation systems. These QoIs directly inform the structural adequacy assessment required for 510(k) submission. The mapping from QoI to clinical consequence (construct failure leading to revision surgery) is explicitly documented in the risk analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (>=3). Validation scenario matches COU geometry, loading, and material.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the COU: identical device geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw), identical loading protocol (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending), identical material system (Ti-6Al-4V), and identical boundary conditions. The validation domain is the COU domain. No extrapolation required. Cross-laboratory reproducibility (FDA vs. DePuy Synthes) further strengthens the relevance assessment."
    }
