    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a medium model-risk, medium decision-consequence application. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged and accepted given: (1) the medium model influence means physical testing is confirmatory rather than replaced by simulation; (2) all three QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance criterion (E/uval < 1.96, percentage difference <10%); (3) cross-laboratory consistency (FDA and DePuy Synthes) provides additional confidence. The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for its intended use in supporting 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
